Title : The Stamp-Collector's Review and Monthly Advertiser
Text : {{Italic title}}
[[File:Stamp Collectors' Review and Monthly Advertiser No 1-1862.png|thumb|upright=1.25|Front cover of first issue of ''Stamp Collectors' Review and Monthly Advertiser'', the world's first dedicated philatelic magazine, initially named ''The Monthly Advertiser'']]
'''''The Stamp-Collector's Review and Monthly Advertiser''''' (originally the ''Monthly Advertiser'' then ''The Stamp-Collector's Monthly Advertiser'') was one of the earliest [[Philatelic literature|philatelic]] [[magazine]]s. It was published by Edward Moore & Co. of Liverpool<ref>{{cite book|title=The Stamp Herald: A Monthly Journal Published in the Interests of Philately and Philatelists|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=8AM9AAAAYAAJ&pg=PA33|year=1918|publisher=B.G. Bushnell|pages=33â€“}}</ref> from 15 December 1862 (Vol. 1, No. 1) to 15 June 1864 (Vol. 2, No. 19).<ref name=birch3>Birch, Brian. ''[http://fipliterature.org/boip.PDF Bibliography of philatelic periodicals]''. 7th edition. Standish, Wigan, Brian Birch, 2013, p. 753-754.</ref> [[Edward Loines Pemberton]] was the [[editor-in-chief|editor]] from January 1864.

